At ModernSam, accessible via
https://modernsam.com/
, safeguarding the privacy of our visitors is a commitment we hold in high regard. This Privacy Policy delineates the kinds of information we gather and the manner in which we employ it.
Should you have any queries or require additional information regarding our Privacy Policy, please do not hesitate to reach out to us at
ryan@modernsam.com
.
This Privacy Policy is exclusively applicable to online activities conducted on our website and pertains solely to information disclosed or gathered through ModernSam. It does not encompass information collected offline or through avenues other than this website.
Consent
By utilizing our website, you express your consent to this Privacy Policy and agree to abide by its provisions.
Information We Collect
We collect personal information when it is deemed necessary for the purpose for which it was provided. When you make direct contact with us, we may gather details such as your name, email address, phone number, the contents of your messages, and any supplementary information you furnish.
In the event that you register for an account, we may request your contact details, which may encompass your name, company name, address, email address, and telephone number.
How We Utilize Your Information
The information we gather serves the following objectives:
Facilitate the operation and maintenance of our website.
Enhance, tailor, and broaden the functionality of our website.
Comprehend and analyze your interaction with our website.
Pave the way for the creation of new products, services, features, and functionalities.
Foster direct communication with you or through our partners, pertaining to customer service, updates, and marketing endeavors.
Dispatch emails to you.
Identify and forestall instances of fraud.
Log Files
At ModernSam, we utilize log files to gather non-personally identifiable information, which includes details like IP addresses, browser types, ISPs, date and time stamps, referring/exit pages, and click data. These log files are employed for trend analysis, site administration, user movement tracking, and demographic data collection.
Cookies and Web Beacons
Similar to many other websites, ModernSam employs cookies to enhance the user experience, tailoring it based on preferences and the pages visited. For more comprehensive information regarding cookies, please consult our [link to Cookies Policy].
Privacy Policies of Advertising Partners
To gain insights into the privacy practices of our advertising partners, we recommend reviewing their respective privacy policies. Third-party advertisers may utilize technologies such as cookies and web beacons to gauge the effectiveness of campaigns and to personalize advertisements. It's important to note that ModernSam lacks control over the cookies employed by third-party advertisers.
Privacy Policies of Third Parties
Please be aware that our Privacy Policy does not extend to cover other advertisers or websites. For detailed information and instructions on opting out, we advise consulting the privacy policies of these third-party services.
You have the option to manage cookies through your browser settings; visit your browser's website for additional information.
CCPA Privacy Rights (Do Not Sell My Personal Information)
California residents hold the following rights:
The right to request disclosure of the categories and specific pieces of personal data collected.
The right to request the deletion of personal data.
The right to opt out of the sale of personal data.
To exercise these rights, please reach out to us.
GDPR Data Protection Rights
All users possess the following rights:
The right to access personal data.
The right to rectify inaccurate data.
The right to erase data under certain conditions.
The right to restrict processing under certain conditions.
The right to object to processing under certain conditions.
The right to data portability under certain conditions.
To exercise these rights, please contact us.
Children's Information
ModernSam does not knowingly collect personal information from children under the age of 13. If you suspect that a child has provided such information, please promptly get in touch with us for its removal.
By utilizing our website, you acknowledge and consent to the provisions outlined in this Privacy Policy. Our commitment is to safeguard your privacy and ensure the security of your personal information. Please note that this policy may undergo periodic updates; we recommend reviewing it from time to time for any revisions.
We appreciate your choice of ModernSam.